  "prompt": "Why did Game of Thrones decide to hire teenagers to play the role of teenagers, rather than youthful-looking adults?",
  "response": "The decision to hire teenagers to play teenager roles in Game of Thrones, as opposed to youthful-looking adults, likely stems from a desire for authenticity and realism. Casting actual teenagers can bring a sense of genuine youthfulness and relatability to the characters, enhancing the viewers' connection to their experiences and growth. Teens bring a different energy and perspective to the roles that can be harder to capture with adults. Additionally, this approach aligns with the characters\u2019 age as described in the source material, George R.R. Martin's \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" series, ensuring that the adaptation is faithful to the books. It can also lend credibility to the storyline by accurately portraying the challenges and dynamics faced by young characters in a complex and often brutal world.",
